          <p>The COVID-19 vaccine Cominarty from BioNTech/Pfizer has been authorized for youths aged 12 and older 
          <a href="https://www.ema.europa.eu/en/medicines/human/EPAR/comirnaty" target="_blank"><i class="fas fa-external-link-alt mr-1"></i>by the European Medicines Agency(EMA)</a>. Cominarty has received a recommendation for youths aged 12 and older <a href="https://www.rki.de/DE/Content/Infekt/Impfen/ImpfungenAZ/COVID-19/Infoblatt_Impfung_Kinder_und_Jugendliche.html" target="_blank"><i class="fas fa-external-link-alt mr-1"></i>from the German Standing Committee on Vaccination (STIKO)</a>.</p>
          <h5 class="mb-3 mt-4">You have the right to medical care as an adolescent</h5>
          <p>As a minor it is advised to consult with your parents or legal guardian before a medical procedure. However, should your parents forbid you to receive a medically necessary procedure, you can receive the procedure without their consent, as provided <a href="https://www.gesetze-im-internet.de/bgb/BJNR001950896.html#BJNR001950896BJNG026900377" target="_blank"><i class="fas fa-external-link-alt mr-1"></i>in the German Patient Rights Law</a>. Don't worry, physicians and youth counsellors are here to guide you along the path.</p>
          <h5 class="mb-3 mt-4">Physicians & youth counsellors are here to help</h5>
          <p>With your consent physicians are allowed to perform medical procedures. The physician will judge the necessity of the procedure and your ability to give consent independently of your parents. If these requirements are fulfilled, the procedure can be performed. If you feel insecure about proceeding without guidance, your local youth counsellors are here to help.</p>
